Secchi (Feet)
Depth Units

column2: Wavy but not white caps.  Very blue skies and no boat traffic.  For Lake Wis- the water seemed very clean.  My husband- Ron Smith- drove our pontoon and helped find the GPS coordinates and the visual markers for next time
light waves and light weekend boat traffic.  This was after a week of heavy rain and wind
Very calm with no boat traffic.  Very weedy in shallow areas.  This was my first test from the kayak and I was not able to anchor but there was no wind and no waves..
slight breeze with slight waves.  Can't anchor my kayak
Calm.  Silver dollar size algae chunks floating

Small waves.  The water is getting more algae by the day.  Worth noting that I am pretty squeamish when it comes to algae so while many people are in the water- apparently enjoying it- I don't even like to kayak next to it. Small waves.  Water is getting dirtier by the day
I did not do the testing because the water was filled with blue green algae and smelled horrible.  In 11 years of living on the lake I have never seen it like this.  I would not even put my kayak in
light breeze.  Last week's algae has dispersed
totally quiet waters - no boats- no waves
Windy with slight waves.  Kidney bean size chunks of algae suspended on the water
From pontoon boat.  Somewhat wavy and windy conditions.  This was 2 days after a huge rainfall and predictions were for the river to crest just north in Portage the next day.
calm - lots of geese.  This is the last test I'll do as our pier is coming out.
Followed 2 days of rain.  This is the cleanest I have seen the lake in 11 years.
1/2" rain last night.  Slightly breezy day
calm with no recent rain.  There is much pollen floating on the surface but otherwise water looks clean
This is my new spot.  43.37178- -89.56638.  Same depth and readings as old spot.  After 2 days of 4+" of rain the lake is smelly.  There are some carp jumping.
weedy with lots of milfoil closer to shore.  very wavy day.
Lots of carp near shore.  Large clumps of algae and lots of milfoil near shore.   The testing hole has lots of dispersed algae.  Slightly breezy day.
smelly with lots of dispersed algae
very calm.  Have not seen so much algae in years.  I found the water disgusting.  Lots of geese gathering in the bay
Very windy and lots of geese
Water temp 71- last week in 90s- Rain had quit - sunny- calm- few boats out
Water 80F- partly sunny- wind 5mph W- hot humid last three days- bluegreen algae starting to appear- sparse- wild celery fragments present
Water 74F- Sunny- light wind SW- past week cool- little rain- slight blue green bloom- river normal
Minimal blue green algae- light SE wind- cooler weather lately- no rain -  main channel has bg algae all way down lake- most of year- places leaves a green wake
